I see just the file mode is updated for couple of files. Is this part of this review?
Good catch. No, those changes were unintentional. Let me fix that.
Done
is it required to catch the exception thrown by next()?

Not according to the code that was already there 😊 The behaviour implemented by this change matches the behaviour that already existed, which is the thrown exception isn't caught. If you want to change that policy we can do that in another patch.

I need us to work with "not worse" as a philosophy and not "strictly better", otherwise you're asking me to put in a lot of effort to change something that's tangential to the goal of the patch.
Ack
here also do we have catch the exceptions?
See the other replies.
